      "question": "If $3\\cot \\theta = 2$, evaluate the value of $\\frac{4\\sin \\theta - 3\\cos \\theta}{2\\sin \\theta + 6\\cos \\theta}$.",
      "answer": "$\\frac{1}{3}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Given $3\\cot \\theta = 2$, find $\\cot \\theta = \\frac{2}{3}$.",
          "Divide numerator and denominator by $\\sin \\theta$ to express in terms of $\\cot \\theta$.",
          "Substitute the value of $\\cot \\theta$ and simplify."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{4\\sin \\theta - 3\\cos \\theta}{2\\sin \\theta + 6\\cos \\theta} = \\frac{4 - 3\\cot \\theta}{2 + 6\\cot \\theta} \\\\ = \\frac{4 - 3(2/3)}{2 + 6(2/3)} \\\\ = \\frac{4-2}{2+4} = \\frac{2}{6} = \\frac{1}{3}$"
      },
