      "question": "If $\\sin \\theta + \\sin^2 \\theta = 1$, prove that $\\cos^2 \\theta + \\cos^4 \\theta = 1$.",
      "answer": "Proof completed.",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "From $\\sin \\theta + \\sin^2 \\theta = 1$, express $\\sin \\theta = 1 - \\sin^2 \\theta$.",
          "Substitute $\\sin \\theta = \\cos^2 \\theta$.",
          "Square both sides to get $\\sin^2 \\theta = \\cos^4 \\theta$ and substitute into the identity."
        ],
