      "question": "Evaluate: $\\frac{\\cos 45^\\circ}{\\sec 30^\\circ + \\csc 30^\\circ}$.",
      "answer": "$\\frac{3\\sqrt{2} - \\sqrt{6}}{8}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Substitute the standard trigonometric values: $\\cos 45^\\circ = 1/\\sqrt{2}$, $\\sec 30^\\circ = 2/\\sqrt{3}$, $\\csc 30^\\circ = 2$.",
          "Simplify the denominator.",
          "Rationalize the resulting expression."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{1/\\sqrt{2}}{2/\\sqrt{3} + 2} = \\frac{1/\\sqrt{2}}{(2 + 2\\sqrt{3})/\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{\\sqrt{2}(2+2\\sqrt{3})} \\\\ = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2\\sqrt{2} + 2\\sqrt{6}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}(2\\sqrt{6}-2\\sqrt{2})}{4(6-2)} = \\frac{6\\sqrt{2}-2\\sqrt{6}}{16} = \\frac{3\\sqrt{2}-\\sqrt{6}}{8}$"
      },
